<item>
            <title>[LU-13529] mkfs.lustre mkfsopts syntax</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13529</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m wondering how mkfs.lustre handles --mkfsopts parameters.&lt;br/&gt;
We have at least -i -I -N options.&lt;br/&gt;
-i &amp;lt;bytes-per-inode&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-I &amp;lt;inode-size&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-N &amp;lt;total number of inodes&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
1. How mkfs.lustre behaves if multiple options specified simultaniously , for example: mkfs.lustre --mkfsoptions=&apos;-i 131072 -N 1073741824 -I 2048&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2.If mkfs.lustre still handles paramtere when option and value are not space-delimited, for example: --mkfsoptions=&apos;-i131072 -N1073741824 -I2048&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="59077">LU-13529</key>
            <summary>mkfs.lustre mkfsopts syntax</summary>
                <type id="9" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/issuetypes/undefined.png">Question/Request</type>
