                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="269755" author="adilger" created="Sat, 9 May 2020 12:15:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using -N is preferred over -i. Using &quot;-I&quot; is independent of the other options, unless it results in an invalid filesystem (eg. -i &amp;lt; -I, or -I x -N &amp;gt; device size). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think it matters if there is a space between the argument and the value or not. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
